<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-567-469  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 567 469.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 24 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for IBM: UK-based Locomotive offers new utilities. (LocomotiveSoftware) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Locomotive Software (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Locoscript PC (Word processing software) (Computer programs)Locofont 34 (Computer font) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionAdd-In-On SoftwareWord processing softwareSoftware packagesFonts.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR IBM: UK-Based Locomotive Offers New Utilities DORKING, ESSEX,ENGLAND, 1990 OCT 24 (NB) -- Locomotive Software has launched two sets ofutilities for Locoscript PC, its recently released PC word processingpackage.andP;  The first set of utility disks are a five-language Europeandictionary, while the second is a set of extra download fonts called Locofont34.andM;Locoscript PC supports all European languages through a system of 'supershifts' which allow the user to type the full range of European, EasternEuropean, Greek, Ancient Greek and Cyrillic characters and accents.andP;  Eachlanguage disk costs UKP 49-95.andM;Locofont 24, meanwhile allows PC users to produce document in various stylessuch as Script, Roman, Copper Plate or Capital fonts on any suitable 24-pinprinter.andP;  The package costs UKP 24- 95.andM;(Steve Gold/19901023/Press Contact: Jane Dagnell, Locomotive Software - Tel:0306-740606)</TEXT></DOC>